'''Emily Corrie''' (born 1978) is a [[United Kingdom|British]] [[Royal Navy]] sailor and former [[actress]]. She is perhaps best known for playing the character Suzanne 'Sooz' Lee in [[Channel 4]]'s teen drama, ''[[As If]]'' and latterly in the American version.
Brought up in [[Chorleywood]], [[Hertfordshire]], after studying at [[London Academy of Music and Dramatic Art]], Corrie won her first screen role in 1999 playing [[Ray Winstone]]'s daughter in the TV series ''Births, Marriages and Deaths''.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.dailymail.co.uk/news/article-1219194/Former-soap-star-Emily-Corrie-swaps-acting-Royal-Navy.html#ixzz0TTtYSlMb|title=Former soap star Emily Corrie swaps acting for the Royal Navy after she passes out as a Wren|author=Simon Cable|publisher=Daily Mail|date=2009-10-09|accessdate=2009-10-09}}</ref>
She was the only actor from the British series of ''As If'' to star in the [[As If (US TV series)|American version]], moving to [[Los Angeles]]. [[McFly]]'s debut number one single "[[5 Colours in Her Hair]]" was an homage to her character 'Sooz'.<ref>[http://news.bbc.co.uk/cbbcnews/hi/chat/hotseat/newsid_3579000/3579127.stm#q2 In the HotSeat - McFly] ''news.bbc.co.uk''</ref>
Corrie also starred in the drama series ''[[NY-LON]]''. In 2007 she had cameo roles in [[BBC One]] shows ''[[Casualty (TV series)|Casualty]]'' and ''[[Doctors (2000 TV series)|Doctors]]''.
Engaged to a Royal Navy sailor and a keen [[Underwater diving|diver]], in 2009 Corrie enlisted in the Royal Navy after becoming disillusioned with life as an actress. She completed her basic training at [[HMS Raleigh (shore establishment)|HMS Raleigh]] in [[Cornwall]], where her passing out ceremony was held in October. As of October 2009, she will undertake another 10 months of training at both [[HMS Collingwood]] in [[Fareham, Hampshire]] and HMS Raleigh.<ref>[http://news.bbc.co.uk/1/hi/england/8297791.stm#q2 TV teen drama actress joins Navy] ''news.bbc.co.uk''</ref><ref>[http://www.dailymail.co.uk/news/article-1219194/Former-soap-star-Emily-Corrie-swaps-acting-Royal-Navy.html Daily Mail news story] Retrieved 2009-10-09</ref>
